                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18460706-1406-offence-1 t18460706-name-105"></join>Matthew Sherborn</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460706-name-106" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-106" type="surname" value="SHERBORN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-106" type="given" value="MATTHEW"></interp>MATTHEW SHERBORN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a farmer, and live at Heston. Thomas Axtin, my servant, sells hay and straw for me—the prisoner was also in my service, and in the absence of Cooper, his fellow workman, it was his business to receive money for me—if he received any money on the 23rd of June, he should have paid it to Axtin.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460706-name-107" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-107" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-107" type="surname" value="AXTIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-107" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS AXTIN</persName>
                  </hi>. It was my business to receive money for everything sold. On the 23rd of June the prisoner paid me 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for his master, for half a load of oat-straw, and a quarter of a load of wheat straw, which he had sold to Samuel Rouse—I am sure that was all he paid me.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184607060008"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> He did not pay you as having sold it himself? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, as sold by Cooper.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460706-name-108" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-108" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-108" type="surname" value="ROUSE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-108" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL ROUSE</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 23rd of June I bought some wheat-straw and and oat-straw of Axtin, and paid him 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 9<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. to Cooper, for Mr. Sherborn.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460706-name-109" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-109" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-109" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460706-name-109" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH COOPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I received 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 9<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., from Rouse for the straw—I am certain I gave the prisoner the whole of it, to take to Axtin.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What description of money was it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> A sovereign, two half-crowns, two shillings, a sixpence, and a fourpenny-piece.</p>
               <p>
